AVGR Im finally all out with a loss Im going to post this a final time to try and save some of you from a big loss Looking at their SEC filings record they received delisting notice in 52017 and reverse split 140 in 13118 They received another delisting notice 12418 and we are coming up on June 11 The date of their meeting to vote the split I would NOT be surprised to see a 110 Reverse split on June 12 19 They word the reverse split a bit sneaky by saying with the exact ratio to be set within that range at the discretion of our board of directors before the day prior to the 2020 annual meeting so everyone is saying no reverse split til 2020 But that is not correct It is saying before that date which means anytime from June 11 19 to that date they can do the split without any further auth Now ask yourself has this company given you any reason to think that they wont do a split that they will request extension They didnt do it before so I say NO
